Health and beauty retailer, Clicks, is in hot water. over images on its website. Many believe they show prejudice against natural black hair. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Clicks a health and beauty retailer in South Africa is in hot water over images on their website. Many believe the images show prejudice against natural black hair. The images sparked outrage on social media. READ: A call for unity against racism The website had pictures of black hair labelled as Dry and Damaged while white hair labelled as Fine and Flat. Clicks have since removed the images and issued an apology saying it’s a strong advocate for natural hair. Watch the video above for more in this story.